begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves with our names, and then we shared how old we were. It then stemmed into part of a conversation with jobs/school.
middle_memory_text: We talked a lot about school as well as what our education was about. And we talked about how we came to want to be our future occupation. It was very insightful to how our education growing up affected our current ideas for higher education.
end_memory_text: We were talking about our hobbies, and then mostly about what we've done with crochet. She talked about making scarves for Christmas and me making small traditional animals.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week is going to be very busy with school. I have a lot of homework due for my Italian class by the end of the week. Im worried about finishing all of it on time, but i am pretty sure I will get it done like always.
critical_positive: I think the biggest thing that worked well is the fact that we had so much in common. While we were at different points in our lives, we still had so much in agreement. It was interesting how much we enjoyed the same things, while still doing very different things.
critical_negative: There really wasn't a lot that didn't work in the conversation. If anything, the biggest thing was that sometimes we interrupted each other when we tried to fill in the lapse of sound. Because we didn't really have a plan for what we would talk about, there were sometimes some unnaturally long pauses.

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves, and asked each other our ages. We then talked about what we study/studied at school and our future plans. We talked about past, current, and future jobs.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we talked about the "dream jobs" we had as children. She mentioned that she was interested in learning about pottery, which drove the conversation towards our crafty hobbies.
end_memory_text: At the end of our conversation, we continued talking about our hobbies. We talked about our experience with crochet. We also talked about a pop-culture icon, Harry Styles, and how a sweater he wore has become popular on TikTok. Finally, we talked about craft deals, and wished each other well with college, careers, and life choices.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will be mostly positive. I have a lot of things to look forward to, like seeing my best friend and her new boyfriend, as well as learning more about my job. I've used today to prepare for the rest of the week, and I see it going smoothly.
critical_positive: We seemed to easily find something to talk about once the conversation started. For example, we could find the next topic of conversation from what the other person said. I feel we had a reciprocal relationship of sharing information, and wanted to learn about the other person. To me, I was surprised when the 25 minute timer we had set rang because it felt like little time had passed.
critical_negative: Because I didn't want to ask personal questions (politics, location, etc.), I found it slightly difficult to know what all to say, or what context to give to my part of the conversation. One thing we talked about briefly at the beginning of the conversation was COVID guidelines and wearing masks. Although, I am pro-masks, I didn't want to start the conversation off by offending her in any way.
